تحميل وتثبيت فلاتر وبرنامج أندرويد استوديو To download and install Flutter in Android Studio, follow these steps:

1. Download and install Android Studio: Visit the official Android Studio website at https://developer.android.com/studio 
   and download the latest version of Android Studio for your operating system. Run the installer and follow the on-screen instructions
   to install it.

2. Set up Android Studio: Open Android Studio after installation and complete the initial setup wizard.
   This includes selecting a UI theme, installing necessary SDK components, and configuring the Android Virtual Device (AVD) manager.

3. Open Android Studio's Preferences: Once Android Studio is open, go to the "Preferences" menu on macOS or the "Settings"
   menu on Windows/Linux.

4. Install the Flutter plugin: In the preferences/settings window, navigate to "Plugins" on the left-hand side.
   Click on the "Marketplace" tab and search for "Flutter." Locate the official Flutter plugin and click the "Install" button.
   Once the installation is complete, click "Restart" to restart Android Studio.

5. Set up Flutter SDK: After restarting, go back to the preferences/settings window. This time, navigate to "Languages & Frameworks"
   and select "Flutter" from the left-hand side menu. Click on the "Enable Flutter SDK" checkbox.
   If you haven't already downloaded the Flutter SDK, click on "Download SDK" to fetch the latest version.
   Provide a path for the Flutter SDK installation and click "Apply" to save the settings.

6. Create a new Flutter project: Now, you can create a new Flutter project. Select "File" from the top menu, navigate to "New,
   " and choose "New Flutter Project." Follow the prompts to set up your project, including providing a project name,
   choosing a Flutter SDK, and selecting an Android device to run the app on.

7. Run the Flutter app: Once your project is set up, you can run your Flutter app. Select the target device from the toolbar,
   click on the play button, or use the "Run" menu option to launch your app on the selected device.

That's it! You have successfully downloaded and installed Flutter in Android Studio. 
You can now start developing Flutter applications using the powerful features and tools provided by Android Studio.
